    <p>
        First, in order to figure out what to change, I wanted to stick to the requirements. Pitchfork publishes
        5 reviews every weekday. the layout shows the current day's reviews with the first album displayed. the detail
        view
        shows the album artwork and album info containing the artist name, album name, author name and
        an excerpt. Hovering over one of the thumbnails triggers a transition, making it the active album.
        There are 5 tabs for the last 5 days of reviews and clicking a tab activates that day's reviews.
    </p>

    <p class="pv++"><strong class="text-highlight">What I wanted to do</strong> was focus on the album art as a strong visual component
        of an otherwise text heavy layout. I've always responded to album artwork and in this digital age we don't get to
        see very much of it. In order to bring the art to the foreground of the component, I decided to conceal the text
        content under the album cover that could be revealed on hover. This not only made it easier on the eyes, it
        became alot more enjoyable to browse. Peep the demo below.
